HOW TO RUN MAHOUT

The test class / files I’ve been using are all in the firstrecommender folder. To compile, set Terminal so you’re in firstrecommender, then use 

mvn compile 

to compile, and 

mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.first.GenericUserBasedRecommender1"

to run.

Here are some sites that have been really helpful for getting this working / understanding what’s going on under the hood :


This one is a tutorial for the test that I did :
http://www.drdobbs.com/open-source/machine-learning-with-apache-mahout-the/240163272?pgno=2


This gets more into how the software works / how to do some of the things we’ll want to do next :
http://www.slideshare.net/Cataldo/tutoria-mahout-recommendation